If a value of true is specified for the includeDeleted flag, then any soft-deleted records will also be considered in the searched records.

get.summary:
Search for organizations/companies in the help desk system, using the provided CEQL search expression. The search expression in CEQL is the WHERE clause in a typical SQL query, but without the WHERE keyword. For example, to search for all companies whose name contains the word 'bug', the search expression parameter will be where=name='%bug%'. Performing a search without these parameters will not return any results.

If a value of true is specified for the includeDeleted flag, then any soft-deleted records will also be considered in the searched records.

parameters.name: Authorization
parameters.description: The authorization tokens. The format for the header value is 'Element <token>, User <user secret>'

parameters.name: where
parameters.description: The CEQL search expression, or the where clause, without the WHERE keyword, in a typical SQL query. For example, to search for incidents last modified on or after 'Jan 15, 2014', the search expression will be where=lastModifiedDate>='2014-01-15T00:00:00.000Z'. When this parameter is omitted, all incidents are returned in a paginated fashion.

parameters.name: includeDeleted
parameters.description: Specify if deleted incidents should be included in the search.

parameters.name: pageSize
parameters.description: The number of results to return per page
